item.content:encoded:
The Versus Project is a community project started on the Envoy forum and is trying to recreate the “golden days” of the dark net (Silk road days). The market focuses on Drugs and less on digital products, so if you are looking for CC or guides you should look elsewhere.

Versus Market has no on-site wallet and push users to use multi sig, which make it less likely for the market to exit scam like many other dark net markets has done in the past.

The post AlphaBay Market appeared first on DarknetMarkets.
item.content:encoded:
AlphaBay first launched in 2014 and became the biggest dark net market quickly, at July 2017 was closed by the FBI and its admin Alexander Cazes caught in Thailand and shortly after committed suicide in Thai prison.
On August 2021, DeSnake the former Co Admin of the original AlphaBay has announced on Dread that AlphaBay is relaunching with a new design and team.

Alphabay is now Monero only market, with automated dispute system and on the i2p network as well as the tor network.
